            ['name' => 'Pakistan', 'description' => 'Pakistan, in South Asia, is rich in history, mountains, and diverse cultural traditions.', 'big_description' => "The Islamic Republic of Pakistan is a South Asian nation covering about 881,000 km², bordered by India, China, Afghanistan, and Iran. With a population exceeding 240 million, Pakistan features diverse landscapes, from the towering peaks of the Karakoram and Himalayas to fertile plains and deserts. The country boasts a deep historical legacy, home to ancient civilizations like the Indus Valley and iconic landmarks such as Mohenjo-daro, Badshahi Mosque, and Lahore Fort. Pakistan’s culture is a fusion of South Asian, Central Asian, and Islamic influences, offering rich traditions in music, art, and cuisine.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/pk.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'Bangladesh', 'description' => 'Bangladesh is a riverine country in South Asia, known for its fertile plains, vibrant culture, and textiles.', 'big_description' => "The People’s Republic of Bangladesh is a South Asian country covering about 148,000 km² and home to more than 170 million people. Situated on the fertile Ganges-Brahmaputra Delta, it is one of the most densely populated nations in the world. Bangladesh is renowned for its rich culture, traditional crafts, and textile industry. Its landscapes are dominated by rivers, mangrove forests, and floodplains, including the Sundarbans, home to the Royal Bengal Tiger. Dhaka, the capital, is a vibrant city that reflects both the challenges and resilience of this fast-growing nation.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/bd.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'Sri Lanka', 'description' => 'Sri Lanka is an island nation in South Asia famous for its beaches, ancient temples, and lush landscapes.', 'big_description' => "The Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka is an island country located in the Indian Ocean, just south of India. Covering about 65,000 km², it features diverse landscapes including tropical rainforests, highlands, and beautiful coastlines. With a population of around 22 million, Sri Lanka boasts a history dating back over 2,500 years, visible in ancient cities like Anuradhapura and Polonnaruwa. The island’s culture blends Buddhist traditions, colonial influences, and local customs. Known for its tea plantations, wildlife, and beaches, Sri Lanka is often called the ‘Pearl of the Indian Ocean.’", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/lk.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'Saudi Arabia', 'description' => 'Saudi Arabia is a Middle Eastern country known as the birthplace of Islam, with vast deserts and modern cities.', 'big_description' => "The Kingdom of Saudi Arabia is a vast country located on the Arabian Peninsula, covering approximately 2.15 million km², making it the largest nation in the Middle East. It is home to over 36 million people and holds great cultural and religious significance as the birthplace of Islam and location of the holy cities Mecca and Medina. The nation’s landscape is dominated by deserts, including the Rub' al Khali, the largest sand desert in the world. Saudi Arabia combines deep-rooted traditions with rapid modernization, seen in its futuristic cities like Riyadh and NEOM.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/sa.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'United Arab Emirates', 'description' => 'The UAE is a Middle Eastern country famous for its futuristic skyline, luxury cities like Dubai, and desert landscapes.', 'big_description' => "The United Arab Emirates is a federation of seven emirates located on the Arabian Peninsula, covering about 83,000 km². With a population of roughly 10 million, the UAE is known for its striking blend of modernity and tradition. Dubai and Abu Dhabi are global hubs of commerce, architecture, and luxury tourism, featuring landmarks such as the Burj Khalifa and Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque. Beyond its cities, the UAE boasts golden deserts, oases, and coastal mangroves. Despite rapid development, the country maintains its Bedouin heritage and strong cultural identity.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ae.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'Qatar', 'description' => 'Qatar is a small, wealthy Gulf nation in the Middle East known for modern architecture, oil wealth, and cultural sites.', 'big_description' => "The State of Qatar is a small but wealthy nation located on the Arabian Peninsula, covering around 11,500 km². With a population of about 3 million, Qatar has become one of the richest countries in the world thanks to its vast natural gas reserves. Its capital, Doha, features cutting-edge architecture, cultural landmarks like the Museum of Islamic Art, and a rapidly growing skyline. Despite its modern transformation, Qatar preserves its traditions through art, falconry, and desert culture. The country gained global attention as the host of the FIFA World Cup 2022.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/qa.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],
            ['name' => 'Israel', 'description' => 'Israel is a Middle Eastern country with deep historical and religious significance, famous for Jerusalem and Tel Aviv.', 'big_description' => "The State of Israel is a small but historically rich nation located on the eastern shore of the Mediterranean Sea, covering about 22,000 km². With a population of over 9 million, Israel holds immense cultural, historical, and religious importance as the birthplace of Judaism and Christianity. Its landscapes range from coastal plains and deserts to the fertile Galilee hills. Jerusalem, one of the world’s oldest cities, is sacred to Jews, Christians, and Muslims alike, while Tel Aviv represents modernity, technology, and a vibrant arts scene. Israel’s blend of history and innovation makes it truly unique.", 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/il.png', 'continent_id' => $asia->id],

