            ['name' => 'Egypt', 'description' => 'Egypt is a North African country famous for its ancient civilization, the pyramids, and the Nile River.', 'big_description' => 'The Arab Republic of Egypt is a country in North Africa, covering 1 million km² with a population of over 100 million. It is famous for its ancient civilization, monumental pyramids, the Sphinx, and the Nile River which has been the lifeblood of Egyptian culture for thousands of years. Egypt blends Pharaonic, Greco-Roman, and Islamic heritage, offering a rich tapestry of history, architecture, and traditions. Its deserts, oases, and vibrant cities like Cairo make it a fascinating country to explore.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/eg.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'South Africa', 'description' => 'South Africa, at the southern tip of the continent, is known for its diverse landscapes, wildlife, and cultural diversity.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of South Africa is located at the southern tip of Africa, covering 1.22 million km² with a population of around 60 million. Known as the “Rainbow Nation,” it features diverse cultures, languages, and religions. Its landscapes range from deserts and mountains to savannas and coastlines. South Africa is famous for wildlife safaris, natural wonders like Table Mountain, and vibrant cities such as Cape Town and Johannesburg. Its rich history includes the legacy of apartheid and a transition to democracy, making it a country of resilience and cultural richness.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/za.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Kenya', 'description' => 'Kenya is an East African country famous for safaris, wildlife reserves, and the Great Rift Valley.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Kenya is an East African nation covering 580,367 km² with a population of over 55 million. Known for its scenic landscapes, Kenya features the Great Rift Valley, savannas, mountains, and lakes. It is home to the “Big Five” wildlife species and numerous national parks and reserves, making it a premier safari destination. Nairobi, the capital, is a modern city blending culture, commerce, and conservation. Kenya’s diverse cultures, languages, and traditions make it a vibrant and fascinating country.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ke.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Nigeria', 'description' => 'Nigeria is Africa’s most populous country, known for its vibrant culture, cities, and music industry.', 'big_description' => 'The Federal Republic of Nigeria is a West African country covering 923,768 km² with a population exceeding 220 million, making it Africa’s most populous nation. Known for its cultural diversity, it has over 500 ethnic groups, each with unique traditions, music, and festivals. Lagos and Abuja are major urban centers, showcasing Nigeria’s rapid development and economic influence. Rich in natural resources and home to Nollywood, one of the world’s largest film industries, Nigeria is a nation of energy, creativity, and resilience.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ng.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Ghana', 'description' => 'Ghana is a West African nation rich in culture, history, and coastal landmarks.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Ghana is a West African country covering 238,533 km² with a population of about 33 million. Ghana is known for its rich history, including powerful ancient kingdoms and the transatlantic slave trade heritage. Its coastline along the Gulf of Guinea features forts and castles, while inland regions offer forests, savannas, and mountains. Accra, the capital, blends tradition and modernity. Ghanaian culture is vibrant, with music, festivals, and cuisine reflecting its diverse ethnic groups and proud heritage.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/gh.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Ethiopia', 'description' => 'Ethiopia is an East African country known for its ancient civilization, highlands, and as the origin of coffee.', 'big_description' => 'The Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia, in the Horn of Africa, covers 1.1 million km² with a population of over 120 million. It is one of the oldest nations in the world, known for its ancient civilizations, rock-hewn churches, and historic cities like Axum and Lalibela. Ethiopia’s highlands, mountains, and plateaus create dramatic landscapes. As the birthplace of coffee, it has a rich cultural and culinary heritage. Ethiopia maintains a unique alphabet, calendar, and traditions, making it a nation with deep historical roots and vibrant culture.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/et.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
