            ['name' => 'Algeria', 'description' => 'Algeria, in North Africa, is known for its vast Sahara Desert, Mediterranean coastline, and historic cities.', 'big_description' => 'The People’s Democratic Republic of Algeria is North Africa’s largest country, covering 2.38 million km² with a population of around 45 million. Algeria is known for the Sahara Desert, Atlas Mountains, and a Mediterranean coastline dotted with historic cities like Algiers and Constantine. The country has a rich history of Berber, Arab, and French influences. Algeria’s culture includes traditional music, cuisine, and festivals, making it a land of natural beauty and cultural depth.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/dz.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Tunisia', 'description' => 'Tunisia is a North African country with Mediterranean beaches, ancient ruins, and desert landscapes.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Tunisia is a North African nation covering 163,610 km² with a population of around 12 million. Tunisia combines Mediterranean beaches, desert landscapes, and historic sites such as Carthage and El Jem amphitheater. Its culture blends Arab, Berber, and French influences, evident in architecture, cuisine, and traditions. The capital, Tunis, is a hub of history and modern life. Tunisia’s diverse geography and rich heritage make it a fascinating destination in North Africa.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/tn.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Tanzania', 'description' => 'Tanzania is an East African country famous for Mount Kilimanjaro, Serengeti National Park, and Zanzibar.', 'big_description' => 'The United Republic of Tanzania, in East Africa, covers 945,087 km² with a population of about 63 million. Tanzania is home to Mount Kilimanjaro, the highest peak in Africa, vast savannas, and the Serengeti National Park, known for wildlife migrations. Its coastal island of Zanzibar is famous for beaches, spice farms, and historic architecture. Tanzania’s culture is diverse, reflecting over 120 ethnic groups with unique traditions, music, and cuisine. It is a country of natural wonders and cultural richness.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/tz.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Uganda', 'description' => 'Uganda is an East African nation known for its lush landscapes, wildlife, and Lake Victoria.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Uganda is an East African country covering 241,038 km² with a population of about 46 million. Known as the “Pearl of Africa,” it features lush forests, savannas, and the source of the Nile River. Uganda is home to diverse wildlife, including mountain gorillas and numerous bird species. Kampala, the capital, is a vibrant cultural and economic center. Uganda’s rich traditions, festivals, and scenic landscapes make it a country of both natural beauty and cultural heritage.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ug.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Zimbabwe', 'description' => 'Zimbabwe, in Southern Africa, is known for Victoria Falls, wildlife, and diverse natural scenery.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Zimbabwe, in Southern Africa, covers 390,757 km² with a population of about 16 million. Famous for Victoria Falls, the country features savannas, mountains, and wildlife-rich national parks. Zimbabwe’s history includes Great Zimbabwe, an ancient city of stone ruins. Harare, the capital, is a cultural and political hub. The country offers rich traditions, music, and cuisine, making it an attractive destination for both natural and cultural exploration.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/zw.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Namibia', 'description' => 'Namibia is a Southern African country famous for the Namib Desert, wildlife, and vast landscapes.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Namibia is located in Southern Africa, covering 825,615 km² with a population of around 2.5 million. Namibia is renowned for its arid Namib Desert, wildlife reserves, and dramatic landscapes such as the Skeleton Coast and Etosha National Park. Windhoek, the capital, blends modern urban life with African traditions. Namibia’s culture, including traditional music, crafts, and heritage, enriches the stunning natural scenery.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/na.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
