            ['name' => 'Cameroon', 'description' => 'Cameroon, in Central Africa, is nicknamed “Africa in miniature” for its diverse landscapes and cultures.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Cameroon is a Central African country covering 475,442 km² with a population of about 27 million. Nicknamed “Africa in miniature,” Cameroon has deserts, mountains, forests, savannas, and beaches, reflecting the continent’s diversity. Its cultural richness includes over 200 ethnic groups with unique traditions, music, and cuisine. Yaoundé, the capital, is the political hub, while Douala is the economic center. Cameroon’s combination of natural beauty and cultural variety makes it a microcosm of Africa.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/cm.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
