            ['name' => 'Ivory Coast', 'description' => 'The Ivory Coast, in West Africa, is famous for cocoa production, beaches, and cultural diversity.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Côte d’Ivoire, or Ivory Coast, is a West African country covering 322,463 km² with a population of about 26 million. It is a leading producer of cocoa and has a rich mix of ethnic groups and traditions. Its landscape includes rainforests, savannas, and coastal beaches. Abidjan, the economic capital, is known for its modern skyline and cultural life. Ivory Coast blends natural resources, cultural diversity, and history into a vibrant national identity.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ci.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Mali', 'description' => 'Mali is a West African country known for Timbuktu, desert landscapes, and rich history.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Mali is a landlocked West African nation covering 1.24 million km² with a population of about 21 million. It is famous for historic cities like Timbuktu, ancient empires, and Saharan landscapes. Mali’s culture includes traditional music, oral history, and crafts. Bamako, the capital, is a center of politics and culture. Mali blends desert beauty, historical significance, and vibrant traditions.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ml.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],
            ['name' => 'Angola', 'description' => 'Angola is a Southern African nation rich in natural resources, wildlife, and coastal scenery.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Angola is located in Southern Africa, covering 1.25 million km² with a population of about 35 million. Angola features coastal plains, highlands, rivers, and savannas. Its economy is rich in oil, diamonds, and other resources. Luanda, the capital, is a cultural and economic hub. Angola’s diverse ethnic groups, music, dance, and traditions contribute to its vibrant national identity, alongside its natural beauty and wildlife.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ao.png', 'continent_id' => $africa->id],

            // North America
            ['name' => 'United States', 'description' => 'The United States is a large and diverse country in North America, known for its cultural influence, varied landscapes, and major cities like New York and Los Angeles.', 'big_description' => 'The United States of America, spanning 9.83 million km² with a population over 330 million, is a North American country renowned for its diversity, innovation, and global influence. It has landscapes ranging from mountains, plains, and deserts to lakes, forests, and coastlines. Major cities like New York, Los Angeles, and Washington D.C. are hubs of finance, culture, and politics. The U.S. has a complex history, including Native American civilizations, European colonization, and a journey to independence. Its culture, economy, and innovation make it a world-leading nation.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/us.png', 'continent_id' => $north_america->id],
            ['name' => 'Canada', 'description' => 'Canada is a vast North American country famous for its wilderness, multicultural cities, and natural wonders like Niagara Falls and the Rocky Mountains.', 'big_description' => 'Canada, covering 9.98 million km² with a population of around 40 million, is the second-largest country in the world. It is known for stunning natural landscapes including forests, lakes, the Rocky Mountains, and the Arctic tundra. Major cities like Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal reflect its multicultural society and high quality of life. Canada has a rich Indigenous and colonial history. Its wildlife, vast wilderness, and vibrant urban centers make it a country of both natural beauty and cultural diversity.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ca.png', 'continent_id' => $north_america->id],
