            ['name' => 'Costa Rica', 'description' => 'Costa Rica is a Central American country famous for its biodiversity, rainforests, and eco-tourism.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Costa Rica is located in Central America, covering 51,100 km² with a population of around 5 million. Costa Rica is renowned for its biodiversity, tropical rainforests, volcanoes, and protected national parks. San José, the capital, is a cultural and economic hub. Costa Rican culture emphasizes peace, sustainability, and environmental stewardship. Its natural beauty, eco-tourism, and friendly people make it a leading destination for nature lovers.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/cr.png', 'continent_id' => $north_america->id],
            ['name' => 'Panama', 'description' => 'Panama is a Central American country known for the Panama Canal, tropical forests, and vibrant culture.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Panama is a Central American nation covering 75,417 km² with a population of about 4.5 million. Panama is known worldwide for the Panama Canal, linking the Atlantic and Pacific oceans. The country has tropical forests, islands, and diverse wildlife. Panama City is a modern metropolis with a mix of history and commerce. Its culture reflects Indigenous, Spanish, and Afro-Caribbean influences. Panama’s geography, history, and culture make it a unique and strategic nation.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/pa.png', 'continent_id' => $north_america->id],
            ['name' => 'Guatemala', 'description' => 'Guatemala is a Central American country known for ancient Mayan ruins, volcanoes, and colorful culture.', 'big_description' => 'The Republic of Guatemala, covering 108,889 km² with a population of about 18 million, is a Central American nation rich in history and natural beauty. Guatemala has volcanoes, rainforests, and highlands, along with ancient Mayan ruins such as Tikal. Guatemala City is the capital and cultural center. Its population features diverse Indigenous groups, each with unique traditions, languages, and crafts. Guatemala’s landscapes, heritage, and vibrant culture make it an extraordinary country to explore.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/gt.png', 'continent_id' => $north_america->id],

