            ['name' => 'Brazil', 'description' => 'Brazil is the largest country in South America, known for the Amazon rainforest, vibrant culture, and iconic cities like Rio de Janeiro.', 'big_description' => 'The Federative Republic of Brazil covers 8.5 million km² with a population exceeding 220 million, making it the largest country in South America. It is famous for the Amazon rainforest, Pantanal wetlands, beaches, and vibrant cities like Rio de Janeiro and São Paulo. Brazil has a rich cultural heritage, blending Indigenous, African, and European influences. Carnival, samba, and football are central to its national identity. Its diverse ecosystems, history, and lively culture make Brazil a captivating destination.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/br.png', 'continent_id' => $south_america->id],
            ['name' => 'Argentina', 'description' => 'Argentina is a South American country famous for tango, beef, Patagonia’s landscapes, and cosmopolitan Buenos Aires.', 'big_description' => 'The Argentine Republic, covering 2.78 million km² with a population of about 45 million, is located in southern South America. Argentina features diverse landscapes including the Andes, Pampas, Patagonia, and Atlantic coastlines. Buenos Aires, the capital, is a cosmopolitan city known for tango, cuisine, and culture. Argentina’s history includes Indigenous peoples, European colonization, and independence movements. Its natural beauty, gastronomy, and cultural traditions make it a compelling destination.', 'image' => 'https://flagcdn.com/w320/ar.png', 'continent_id' => $south_america->id],
